Description:
The Covert AT&T Network Ready Code Black 12.1 Scouting Camera offers a number of features to make scouting easy. Features include adjustable camera sensitivity, customizable trigger intervals and start-stop times. In cases where you feel the camera is not catching animals that are nearby or it's triggering too early you can adjust the sensitivity. In most conditions, the N option for 10°F to 80°F works best. However there are H(>80°F) and L(<10°F) settings for different outdoor temperatures. Customize how often the camera can be allowed to take a photo by adjusting the trigger interval. Options are 5-60 seconds (5 second increments) and 1-60 minutes.

The Code Black 12.1 Scouting Camera offers:
  • Start-Stop time in a 24hr format
  • Time lapse option
  • Adjustable trigger interval
  • Adjustable sensitivity

Description:
The SPYPOINT FORCE-11D Game Camera captures 11 megapixel photos or HD videos in color by day & black-and-white by night. The camera uses high-power super low glow LEDs combined with the blur reduction technology to have the best image quality at night. It is the perfect camera to avoid disturbing or spooking your game. The curved motion sensor lens improves the detection angle and distance of its 5 detection zones. The detection range can also be adjusted from 5' to 80'.
